{{ Infobox V8 Supercar race report | flag = Tasmania | title = 2013 Tasmania Microsoft Office 365 | round_no = 2 | season_no = 14 | year = 2013 | series = IVSC | track_map = Symmons Plains Raceway (Australia) track map.svg | date = 5–7 April | location = [[Launceston, Tasmania|Launceston]], [[Tasmania]] | circuit = Symmons Plains Raceway | weather = Fine | race1_laps = 50 | race1_dist = 120 | pole1 = [[Jamie Whincup]] | pole1_team = [[Triple Eight Race Engineering (Australia)|Triple Eight Race Engineering]] | pole1_time = 51.1057 | winner1 = [[Fabian Coulthard]] | winner1_team = [[Brad Jones Racing]] | winner1_time = 1:17:41.5215 | race2_laps = 42 | race2_dist = 100 | pole2 = [[Jason Bright]] | pole2_team = [[Brad Jones Racing]] | pole2_time = 51.1940 | winner2 = [[Jason Bright]] | winner2_team = [[Brad Jones Racing]] | winner2_time = 40:33.8545 | race3_laps = 42 | race3_dist = 100 | pole3 = [[Mark Winterbottom]] | pole3_team = [[Ford Performance Racing]] | pole3_time = 51.2052 | winner3 = [[Fabian Coulthard]] | winner3_team = [[Brad Jones Racing]] | winner3_time = 42:20.8286 }}
The '''2013 [[Falken Tasmania Challenge|Tasmania Microsoft Office 365]]''' was a motor race meeting for the Australian sedan-based [[V8 Supercars]]. It was the second event of the [[2013 International V8 Supercars Championship]]. It was held on the weekend of 5–7 April at the [[Symmons Plains Raceway]], near [[Launceston, Tasmania|Launceston]], [[Tasmania]].
The race meeting was the first to feature the new for 2013 format of a half-time concept in a motor race. The first of the meeting's three races was halted after 25 of 50 laps for a break of approximately 20 minutes before regridding and restarting.
