{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Smart Choice Moosa Stadium | nickname = Smart Choice Stadium | image = | caption = | country = USA | location = [[Pearland]], [[Texas]] | coordinates = {{Coord|29.51768|-95.32565|type:landmark_region:US-TX|display=inline,title}} | establishment = 2015 | seating_capacity = 2,000 | owner = [[Smart Choice]] | operator = [[American College Cricket]] |architect = n/a | tenants = [[American College Cricket]] | end1 = n/a | end2 = | international = flase | firstodidate = | firstodiyear = | firstodihome = | firstodiaway = | date = | year = | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/29/12593.html Ground Page }} '''Smart Choice Moosa Stadium''' is a private cricket stadium in [[Pearland]], [[Texas]].<ref> [http://americancollegecricket.com/2014/12/18/smart-choice-moosa-stadium-is-now-an-american-college-cricket-home-stadium/ MART CHOICE MOOSA STADIUM IS NOW AN AMERICAN COLLEGE CRICKET HOME STADIUM!]</ref><ref>[http://americancollegecricket.com/2014/08/31/new-stadium-hosts-american-college-cricket-sw-chship-register-for-mase-sw/The 5th American College Cricket Mid Atlantic Championship]</ref> The stadium is owned by [[Smart Choice]], a former sponsor of the [[United States national cricket team]]. The stadium has a turf wicket and is being built according to the [[International Cricket Council]] rules as a venue for international cricket. There are three other turf wicket fields being made right next to the Stadium and it has got practice wicket, Stands, Dressing rooms, picnic areas too. It is named after Smart Choice CEO [[Sakhi Muhammad]]’s father. It is home for [[American College Cricket]].
In April 2015, it was announced that [[Canada cricket team]] travel to [[Houston]] to play three warm-up matches against an invitational XI ahead of the [[2015 ICC Americas Twenty20 Division One|ICC Americas Division One T20]] tournament.<ref> [http://www.espncricinfo.com/usa/content/story/864289.html Canada T20 squad to play warm-ups in Texas]</ref>
